The paper deals with detecting spam in social networking services, specifically in Twitter. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also proposes classification schemes for detecting spam, which falls under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The paper also deals with the issue of credibility and reliability of services, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also utilizes social network analysis techniques, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with online relationships and community formations, which falls under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
